verses.text: O give thanks unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*; call upon his name : make known his deeds among the people. \q1
Sing unto him, sing psalms unto him: talk ye of all his wondrous works. \q1
Glory ye in his holy name : let the heart of them rejoice that seek the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*. \q1
Seek the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and his strength : seek his face evermore. \q1
Remember his marvellous works that he hath done ; his wonders , and the judgments of his mouth ; \q1
O ye seed of Abraham his servant , ye children of Jacob his chosen. \q1
He \add is\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God : his judgments \add are\add* in all the earth. \b \q1
He hath remembered his covenant for ever , the word \add which\add* he commanded to a thousand generations. \q1
Which \add covenant\add* he made with Abraham , and his oath unto Isaac ; \q1
And confirmed the same unto Jacob for a law , \add and\add* to Israel \add for\add* an everlasting covenant : \q1
Saying , Unto thee will I give the land of Canaan , the lot of your inheritance :\f + \fr 105.11 \ft lot: Heb. cord\f* \q1
When they were \add but\add* a few men in number ; yea, very few , and strangers in it. \q1
When they went from one nation to another, from \add one\add* kingdom to another people ; \q1
He suffered no man to do them wrong : yea, he reproved kings for their sakes; \q1
\add Saying\add*, Touch not mine anointed , and do my prophets no harm. \q1
Moreover he called for a famine upon the land : he brake the whole staff of bread. \q1
He sent a man before them, \add even\add* Joseph , \add who\add* was sold for a servant : \q1
Whose feet they hurt with fetters : he was laid in iron :\f + \fr 105.18 \ft he…: Heb. his soul came into iron\f* \q1
Until the time that his word came : the word of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* tried him. \q1
The king sent and loosed him; \add even\add* the ruler of the people , and let him go free. \q1
He made him lord of his house , and ruler of all his substance :\f + \fr 105.21 \ft substance: Heb. possession\f* \q1
To bind his princes at his pleasure ; and teach his senators wisdom. \q1
Israel also came into Egypt ; and Jacob sojourned in the land of Ham. \q1
And he increased his people greatly ; and made them stronger than their enemies. \b \q1
He turned their heart to hate his people , to deal subtilly with his servants. \q1
He sent Moses his servant ; \add and\add* Aaron whom he had chosen. \q1
They shewed his signs among them, and wonders in the land of Ham.\f + \fr 105.27 \ft his…: Heb. words of his signs\f* \q1
He sent darkness , and made it dark ; and they rebelled not against his word. \q1
He turned their waters into blood , and slew their fish. \q1
Their land brought forth frogs in abundance , in the chambers of their kings. \q1
He spake , and there came divers sorts of flies , \add and\add* lice in all their coasts. \q1
He gave them hail for rain , \add and\add* flaming fire in their land.\f + \fr 105.32 \ft them…: Heb. their rain hail\f* \q1
He smote their vines also and their fig trees ; and brake the trees of their coasts. \q1
He spake , and the locusts came , and caterpillers , and that without number , \q1
And did eat up all the herbs in their land , and devoured the fruit of their ground. \q1
He smote also all the firstborn in their land , the chief of all their strength. \q1
He brought them forth also with silver and gold : and \add there was\add* not one feeble \add person\add* among their tribes. \q1
Egypt was glad when they departed : for the fear of them fell upon them. \q1
He spread a cloud for a covering ; and fire to give light in the night. \q1
\add The people\add* asked , and he brought quails , and satisfied them with the bread of heaven. \q1
He opened the rock , and the waters gushed out ; they ran in the dry places \add like\add* a river. \q1
For he remembered his holy promise , \add and\add* Abraham his servant. \q1
And he brought forth his people with joy , \add and\add* his chosen with gladness :\f + \fr 105.43 \ft gladness: Heb. singing\f* \q1
And gave them the lands of the heathen : and they inherited the labour of the people ; \q1
That they might observe his statutes , and keep his laws. Praise ye the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 105.45 \ft Praise…: Heb. Hallelujah\f*
